    "notes": "Abruzzese. Southern Italo-Romance of Abruzzo and Molise. Part of the upper Southern Italian (Neapolitan) dialect continuum. ~1.5 million speakers. Key features: (1) Very strong vowel reduction (unstressed finals → [ə]). (2) Productive metaphony (vowel harmony). (3) Gemination preserved. (4) /ʃ/ in consonant clusters (Avolio 1995, Ledgeway 2009).",
